About Munger University

Shri Arif Mohammad Khan  
Prof. (Dr.) Sanjoy Kumar  
Prof. Ghanshyam Roy  
Previous Next

Seeing is believing. Believing is comprehension. And comprehension becomes reality when it becomes functional. When Chief Minister Nitish Kumar, on August 16, 2016, visualized the concept of Munger University, during one of his development tours, nobody knew it will become a reality within a span of two years.

Munger University is a state university and was established through bifurcation of Tilka Manjhi Bhagalpur University, Bhagalpur. It has jurisdiction spreading over five districts: Munger, Lakhisarai, Sheikhpura, Jamui and Khagaria under Munger Division in Bihar.

From Chancellor’s Desk

  • Hon'ble Shri Arif Mohammed Khan, the current Governor of Bihar is the Chancellor of Munger University, as per Acts of the Universities. He was Born on 18 November 1951 Shri Arif Mohammed Khan has done Graduation in Arts from Aligarh Muslim University, Uttar Pradesh and LLB Form Lucknow University, Uttar Pradesh.
